<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1508,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,334,1509,1535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Measurements.</emphasis>
Body length (including forewing): male 
<quantity box="[804,939,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" unit="mm" value="5.15" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="5.1">5.1-5.2 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[1037,1172,1508,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" unit="mm" value="5.35" valueMax="5.4" valueMin="5.3">5.3-5.4 mm</quantity>
; forewing length: male 
<quantity box="[151,285,1545,1571]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.4" valueMin="4.3">4.3-4.4 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[379,512,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="142" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="4.5">4.5-4.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1508,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1580,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellow-brown, vertex with black spots along anterior margin, and with two irregular orange markings behind the spots (
<figureCitation box="[459,560,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellowish brown, ocelli white (
<figureCitation box="[988,1091,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
). Face brown, black transverse streaks and a yellow longitudinal band. Antennae pale yellowish white. Anteclypeus yellowish brown with apex dark-brown (
<figureCitation box="[298,402,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 3, 5</figureCitation>
). Pronotum brownish yellow, with 6 yellowish brown longitudinal markings (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1363,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Scutellum yellowish brown, basal and lateral angles pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[855,927,1724,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Forewings yellowish-brown, with irregular fuscous markings, viens yellowish-white, apical part of forewings pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1127,1760,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Legs with dark spots (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal genital segment pale yellowish white (
<figureCitation box="[834,917,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1415,1439]" captionTargetBox="[154,1428,181,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1391]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 13. Female abdominal sternum VII, ventral view; 14. First valvula, lateral view; 15. Apex of first valvula, lateral view; 16. Second valvula, lateral view; 17. Apex of second valvula, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435680/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1508,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,407,1833,1859]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
External features as in generic description. Crown shorter medially than width between eyes (0.54:1) (
<figureCitation box="[255,356,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
). Pronotum longer medially than crown (1.56:1) (
<figureCitation box="[910,979,1868,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Scutellum shorter medially than pronotum (0.82:1) (
<figureCitation box="[307,376,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Forewing longer than width at widest part (3.17:1) (
<figureCitation box="[977,1079,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1508,2039]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1940,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Male pygofer broad triangular in lateral view, apex tapered, with three stout setae along dorsocaudal margin, ventro-posterior margin with short appendage curved upward (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1125,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1350,1422,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="142">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate short and broad, lateral and apical margins convex except for slight preapical lateral concavity, with row of macrosetae extended obliquely from lateral to mesal margin near midlength (
<figureCitation box="[1099,1168,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus asymmetric and twisted in ventral view, base robust, shaft medially on dorsal side with a short spine, apex curved to the left, gonopore subapical (
<figureCitation box="[384,500,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Figs 9–10</figureCitation>
). Connective nearly X-shaped, arms longer than stem (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1193,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1911,1935]" captionTargetBox="[156,1428,314,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-94@2.[151,1436,306,1885]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 1. Male habitus, dorsal view; 2. Male habitus, lateral view; 3. Face; 4. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 5. Head and thorax, lateral view; 6. Male pygofer, lateral view; 7. Genital valve; 8. left subgenital plate, ventral view; 9. Aedeagus, ventral view; 10. Aedeagus, lateral view; 11. Connective, dorsal view; 12. Left style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435676/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
