<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1521,2015]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1521,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Female seventh sternum with posterior margin broadly transverse between pair of short, rounded lateral lobes. First valvula curved, tapering apically with concatenate sculpture extended to dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,290,1593,1620]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1415,1439]" captionTargetBox="[154,1428,181,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1391]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 13. Female abdominal sternum VII, ventral view; 14. First valvula, lateral view; 15. Apex of first valvula, lateral view; 16. Second valvula, lateral view; 17. Apex of second valvula, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435680/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Figs 14–15</figureCitation>
). Second valvula moderately slender through most of length, gradually tapered distally, dorsal margin with approximately 19 short, simple, acute teeth more or less evenly spaced over distal half, with hyaline region extended obliquely across middle and along ventral margin to distal fourth (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1131,1665,1692]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1415,1439]" captionTargetBox="[154,1428,181,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1391]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Neurotettix spinas sp. nov. 13. Female abdominal sternum VII, ventral view; 14. First valvula, lateral view; 15. Apex of first valvula, lateral view; 16. Second valvula, lateral view; 17. Apex of second valvula, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4435680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4435680/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="144">Figs 16–17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
